  "prompt": "How is condition of Hindus in Pakistan?",
  "response": "The condition of Hindus in Pakistan is generally challenging and characterized by:\n\n1. Minority Discrimination\n- Religious persecution\n- Social marginalization\n- Limited political representation\n- Facing systemic discrimination\n\n2. Population Status\n- Approximately 2-3% of Pakistan's total population\n- Concentrated mainly in Sindh province\n- Declining population due to migration and conversion\n\n3. Social Challenges\n- Limited economic opportunities\n- Lower social status\n- Forced conversions\n- Targeted violence and harassment\n- Restricted access to education and jobs\n\n4. Legal Vulnerabilities\n- Blasphemy laws often misused against religious minorities\n- Inadequate legal protection\n- Difficulty in seeking justice\n\n5. Cultural Pressures\n- Social pressure to convert to Islam\n- Restrictions on religious practices\n- Limited religious freedom\n\n6. Land and Property Rights\n- Frequent land grabbing\n- Challenges in property ownership\n- Economic marginalization\n\n7. Positive Developments\n- Some constitutional protections\n- Increasing awareness about minority rights\n- Some efforts by civil society organizations\n\nOverall, Hindus in Pakistan face significant challenges related to religious, social, and economic discrimination, though the situation varies across different regions and contexts.",
